an arrow was shot at a greyhound bus friday as 
it was leaving a cleveland terminal en route to pittsburgh police 
said 
there were no injuries and no arrests said police lt martin 
flask 
flask said the bus carrying 59 passengers was leaving the 
terminal at about 240 am when the arrow embedded in a window on 
the passenger side four rows from the door he didnt know whether 
it shattered the window 
the driver didnt report the incident until he had the bus on 
the interstate when he radioed his dispatcher flask said 
about 6300 drivers and 3000 other workers at the dallasbased 
company went on strike march 2 
greyhound does not plan to resume talks until attacks against 
buses driven by replacement workers stops and the union softens its 
wage demands said company spokesman george gravley 
he said there have been 20 shootings since the strike started 
with no serious injuries reported 
