<TEXT>
a column of about 100 military vehicles 
rolled through the lithuanian capital before dawn saturday in what 
apparently was another bid by the kremlin to unnerve leaders of the 
breakaway republic 
lithuanian leaders condemned the maneuver and accused the soviet 
union of waging psychological warfare against the small baltic 
republic which declared independence on march 11 
nervous lithuanian legislators passed a resolution transferring 
power to the senior diplomat of independent lithuania in washington 
in case of emergency and several of them walked about 100 yards 
from legislative chambers to a highway overpass to watch the column 
rumble through the city at 4 am 
this is absurd armored vehicles dont usually drive through 
the middle of town in the middle of the night lithuanian prime 
minister kazimeira prunskeine told reporters at the legislature 
were not afraid but we dont know what they want and we 
dont know what they will do in the next few hours she said 
the convoy moved along the main highway through the heart of 
vilnius in the early morning darkness without stopping 
a spokesman for the lithuanian parliament said he had seen the 
convoy pull into a military base at siaures miestelis on the north 
side of the capital 
audris butkavicius a lithuanian deputy who said he talked to 
some of the soldiers said they told him there were about 1000 
paratroopers in the column 
there were at least 22 tanks and armored personnel carriers and 
dozens of green military trucks the parliaments information 
deparment quoting witnesses said there were 59 tanks and 50 other 
vehicles 
deputies who were still meeting in the supreme council 
legislature to finish forming their independent government said 
they had not been notified in advance of the convoys movement 
after deputies checked out the columns movement they broke up and 
began to go home 
gorbachev and his advisers have pledged not to use force to halt 
lithuanias formation of an independent government but lithuanians 
are concerned the soviet military will forcibly try to detain 
soldiers who deserted and returned to their native land after the 
declaration of independence saturday was the deadline for them to 
return to their units 
a top military adviser to soviet president mikhail s gorbachev 
marshal sergei f akhromeyev indicated friday the military would 
try to round up the deserters even if some people dont like 
it 
gorbachev also told the republics president vytautus 
landsbergis on thursday that lithuania should stop signing up 
volunteer forces and sought a response from the lithuanian leader 
within two days 
landsbergis in an early morning telegram to moscow said the 
volunteers would not replace soviet kgb border guards and uniformed 
police as gorbachev suggested the lithuanians would 
speaking about saturdays maneuvers landsbergis said tension 
is rising with this demonstration of military force with this 
frightening of people with soviet soldiers 
in washington white house spokesman marlin fitzwater said 
friday afternoon the situation appears to progressively get 
worse 
the republic is working to restore the independence lost to 
stalins army in 1940 
us officials said the soviet union had ordered two american 
consular officers out of lithuania giving them 12 hours to leave 
us officials said other foreign diplomats and some journalists 
also had been told to leave the lithuanian capital 
the diplomats leningradbased consuls douglas wake and jon 
purnell said friday night in vilnius that they had heard nothing 
about the order for them to leave 
while fitzwater said the diplomats will comply he said the 
united states was not given a reason by moscow for the 
expulsion he said the soviet chief of protocol relayed the 
expulsion notice to officials at the us embassy in moscow 
he said the two officials were in vilnius on routine reporting 
and analysis as they do for the embassy 
they are staff people in our consulate in leningrad he 
said theyre not spies 
wake the us diplomat said us officials regularly traveled 
to lithuania in the course of their consular work but declined to 
comment further on his mission there 
later friday fitzwater said it was unclear what specific 
actions have been taken against journalists but we are opposed to 
any infringements on freedom of the press 
soviet officials on friday continued to increase their pressure 
on lithuania to renounce its declaration of independence from the 
soviet union 
the soviet union informed poland it was suspending visafree 
travel for poles and lithuanians across the border the official 
tass news agency said 
a military helicopter with a soviet red star emblazoned on its 
side dumped leaflets on downtown vilnius containing a copy of 
gorbachevs directive that the republic of 38 million respect 
soviet law 
foreign ministry officials said soviet embassies would review 
foreigners visa applications to travel to lithuania to keep out 
people inclined to engage in illegal activities tass said it 
did not elaborate 
the soviet union forcibly annexed lithuania latvia and estonia 
a halfcentury ago as part of an agreement between josef stalin and 
adolf hitler 
president bush said friday that any attempt by the soviets to 
intimidate lithuania or to use force is bound to backfire that 
is inevitable 
lithuania issued an appeal to the world for support late 
thursday 
