<TEXT>
a federal agency overseeing part of the 
savings and loan bailout last year awarded a 49000 nobid 
contract to an attorney who had pressed regulators not to seize the 
california thrift that later suffered a 2 billion failure 
margery waxman was awarded the fivemonth contract by mary k 
bush the acting director of the federal housing finance board one 
of several agencies established under the sampl bailout plan to 
regulate the nations 12 regional federal home loan banks 
the finance board replaced the federal home loan bank board in 
1988 waxman represented the lincoln savings and loan when the bank 
boards san francisco office was urging its washington headquarters 
to seize the thrift 
in a may 1988 letter to lincolns owner charles keating waxman 
said she had lobbied board officials and told keating you have 
the board right where you want them 
waxman worked with ms bush in the early 1980s at the treasury 
department the waxman contract was one of three ms bush awarded 
last year without competition to longtime friends 
the housing board is overseen by the department of housing and 
urban development and its chairman is hud secretary jack kemp hud 
officials said friday that kemp met with ms bush this week and 
told her he was cutting her powers and assuming final authority for 
all agency contract awards 
a 37000 nobid consulting contracts went to wendell w gunn 
who was kemps chief of staff for several months last year the 
third was a 100000 contract with an atlanta management consulting 
firm whose partners include kevin coyne also a former colleague of 
ms bushs at the treasury department work on all three has been 
completed 
a spokesman for ms bush said she awarded the contracts because 
she knew the recipients had the expertise to help the agency the 
contracts were not put out for bid because the housing finance 
board receives no tax dollars and so is not subject to competitive 
procurement guidelines 
kemps top deputy hud undersecretary alfred dellibovi said 
friday that kemp was not aware of the contracts until this week 
dellibovi said kemp knew gunn was advising ms bush but did not 
know he was being paid and would not have approved of such an 
arrangement because of gunns past work at hud 
dellibovi said kemp continues to support ms bush whose 
expected appointment as chairwoman has not been announced by the 
white house some seven months after the agency was created 
the name of waxman of the washington office of the law firm 
sidley amp austin surfaced in connection with the lincoln case last 
week when house banking committee chairman henry gonzalez dtexas 
released her letter to keating and said it suggested a fix was 
in at the bank board 
in the letter waxman told keating she successfully lobbied m 
danny wall then the director of the nowdefunct board 
as you know i have put pressure on wall to work toward 
meeting your demands and he has so instructed his staff waxman 
wrote 
ten days later despite recommendations from its san francisco 
office the bank board declined to take action against the thrift 
and took the unusual step of shifting oversight responsibilities 
from san francisco to washington 
wall last week denied being pressured by waxman and her law firm 
denied any impropriety 
keating has gained notoriety because of his large contributions 
to five senators who intervened with regulators on his behalf 
