addressing racial stereotypes called across ethnic lines 
students in about 30 classrooms from moscow idaho to lima peru 
will take part 
wheelwright high school students still busy on their 
environmental project wont be participating in the ethnic 
project but just by participating in breadnet they have helped 
weaken their own stereotype of eastern kentucky as a region of 
illiterate hillbillies said slone 
they realize theyre just like all other students all over the 
world said slone 
