here is a look at sundays hungarian election 
at stake 
there are 386 seats in the parliament or national assembly 
elected for a fouryear term an additional eight seats will be 
allotted to the eight main national minorities 
eligible voters and rules 
there are more than 78 million eligible voters choosing from 
among 29 parties only 12 parties are running nationally and the 
17 others are contesting only a few races twentyone parties 
fielded no candidates a second round of voting is mandatory if no 
party wins an absolute majority runoff elections are also possible 
in individual races where there is no clear majority 
all hungarian citizens who have reached 18 years of age by 
march 25 or are considered adults because they are married are 
eligible to vote 
election supervision 
the viennabased international helsinki human rights 
association has a delegation in hungary monitoring the election 
