<TEXT>
art lovers saw empty spaces on the walls saturday 
as the gardner museum reopened two rooms hardest hit by last weeks 
multimilliondollar art theft that has left curators worried about 
protecting works to valuable even to be insured 
the fbi has circulated composite sketches of the two thieves 
two international auction houses have posted a 1 million reward 
for information leading to the return of the works and the museum 
has received tips on their whereabouts 
the fbi has asked museum officials not to comment on the 
investigation for fear of slowing it a museum spokesman said but 
curators elsewhere are not optimistic sometimes they say art not 
recovered soon after being stolen doesnt resurface for years 
