has produced its share of factions in congress over how to allocate 
us dollars for groups fighting the sovietbacked government 
as rep charles wilson dtexas jokingly put it the only way 
to get everyone back under the same tent is to bring the red army 
back 
at issue is not only how the cia spends 600 million a year in 
taxpayer money on covert operations against the government headed 
by najibullah but also whether to continue that level of aid 
the united states began supplying weapons to afghan rebels after 
the soviet union sent troops into afghanistan in late 1979 
although soviet troops pulled out of afghanistan last year 
najibullah remains in power 
the dispute has focused in particular on the amount of aid being 
received by gulbaddin hekmatyar the leader of one of seven rebel 
factions in addition to complaints that the aid is being 
distributed unfairly is one that hekmatyar is a soviet agent 
the question of where hekmatyars allegiances lie was raised by 
