<TEXT>
stasys lozoraitis jr is fluent in half a 
dozen languages russian is not one of them though he confesses a 
desperate need to know it still it is a question of 
principle he says 
lozoraitis is the man in charge of the musty 40room mansion on 
16th street a mile from the soviet embassy which serves as the 
legation of free lithuania as it has for nearly 70 years but for 
the last 50 of those years lithuania was not free 
two sundays ago the building was filled as the lithuanian 
legislature pondered a declaration of independence from the soviet 
union whose troops overran the nation in 1940 i think all the 
500 washington lithuanians came said lozoraitis little 
children holding balloons men and women bringing whiskey bottles 
cookies or just smiles poles though not yet those from their 
embassy down the block estonians latvians armenians 
americans 
and then the news arrived sent via a fax machine that 
lithuanias new president vytautus landsbergis had smuggled home 
after visiting lozoraitis a old school chum in washington last 
summer 
the vote was for freedom cried lozoraitis with that the 
celebration began 
another message arrived saturday the legislature had formally 
declared that its power would fall symbolically to the washington 
legation and lozoraitis if the soviets crush the new government 
a similar role was occupied for 45 years by lozoraitis father 
until his death at age 88 five years ago just days before the 
soviet troops arrived in 1940 free lithuanias last foreign 
minister had sent this message to his embassies if catastrophe 
strikes please consider stasys lozoraitis chief of our nations 
diplomatic corps 
the elder lozaraitis using gold reserves transferred from 
lithuania to sweden as the soviets moved in ran not only the 
washington legation and four us consulates but diplomatic 
outpostsinexile in the vatican great britain canada and 
venezuela according to his son it has been the only diplomatic 
service in history to hold to its mission for more than a half 
century after its country was conquered 
for 50 years said stasys lozoraitis jr we have carried 
on working living dying it is such a pity my father isnt here 
to see all our efforts come to such a conclusion 
throughout the legation are symbols of hope above the fireplace 
in the great hall hangs a painting of a white knight the national 
symbol a mural of the 600yearold nations 1918 declaration of 
independence adorns the front hall on a whiteskirted table in the 
grand salon an old photograph depicts lozoraitss bearded 
grandfather a politician and philosopher with the grandfather 
of landsbergis 
lozoraitis who declines to give his age had just entered his 
teens when his father a former foreign minister was sent off to 
italy ahead of the invading soviet tanks 
in italy the son helped his father with diplomatic reports he 
says he was 15 when he decoded his first cipher but resisted 
diplomacy as a career he wanted to fight and he did as a member 
of an underground group which rescued jews and american prisoners 
of war 
as far as my family was concerned i was absolutely 
irresponsible he recently told the washington post we would 
put these people in cars and drive them to catholic monasteries or 
convents or the vatican i was arrested once by the germans but 
through friends my father saved me 
his exploits during the war also took him back into the baltic 
states and he acknowledges that he has since visited lithuania 
more than once though not officially i would not go to the 
soviet embassy to ask for a visa to my own country he said 
before taking over for his father in washington the son was a 
journalist for vision an international economics magazine and 
learned several languages along the way but not russian it is a 
question of principle and i am sorry because i need it very 
much he said 
in a recent interview with the macneillehrer news hour 
lozoraitis expressed the belief that soviet leader mikhail 
gorbachev will hold true to his pledge not to use force against the 
new lithuanian government 
we are not threatening the political position of gorbachev 
he said if he lets us go his stature as a political figure will 
only increase and he will remain in history 
but saturday the soviet foreign ministry ordered foreign 
diplomats out of lithuania and a military convoy rumbled through 
the vilnius the capital and lozoraitis was left to pray that he 
will not have to take the symbolic torch of power a nervous 
legislature was prepared to bestow upon him 
the state department for years has tiptoed around the 
legations status the united states has never recognized the 
forcible incorporation of estonia latvia and lithuania into the 
soviet union and throughout the cold war has called upon moscow to 
release its captive nations on the other hand it has not 
accredited the diplomatic corpsinexile headed by lozoriatis nor 
has it recognized the new government 
