from honduras continue and that weapons are being hidden 
the editorial also pointed out that contra military chief israel 
galeano cornejo known as commander franklyn had not signed the 
pact for disbanding the rebels 
he took part in the seven hours of talks but his deputy oscar 
sovalbarro signed the accord antonio lacayo mrs chamorros 
representative signed for the incoming leadership of the united 
national opposition the document was witnessed by cardinal miguel 
obando y bravo the roman catholic archbishop of managua 
sovalbarro later told reporters about 12000 rebel fighters and 
their families living in honduran jungle camps planned to start 
demobilizing over the weekend 
the accord also calls for observers from the united nations and 
the organization of american states to supervise the disbanding and 
resettlement of the rebels and their families 
