we intend to have that tradition continue yeutter said 
three food aid programs are most likely to be considered during 
the farm bill debate he said those include the food for peace or 
pl 480 program which provides up to 8 million metric tons of 
commodities to developing countries each year 
others are the food for progress program which authorizes both 
credit sales and donations to help developing countries establish 
privatesector economies and section 416b which authorizes 
additional donations of surplus commodities owned by the 
agriculture department 
yeutter said the proposals include a change in food for peace 
title i operations to allow direct grants at the discretion of the 
president for countries that meet the poverty criteria established 
by the world bank for civil works preference currently those with 
per capita incomes of 545 a year or less 
