a taiwanese fish broker who admitted arranging to 
smuggle 500 tons of illegally caught salmon into this country was 
sentenced friday to nearly six years in prison 
patrick lee 42 whose arrest july 18 was part of a dual action 
on the high seas and outside a major seattle bank also was ordered 
by us district judge carolyn r dimmick to pay 66000 in 
restitution but the judge said that amount might be reduced by the 
amounts five others are ordered to pay when they are sentenced 
no further fine will be imposed because he is unable to pay 
