international investors have many motivations 
for backing us government bonds sometimes single factors such 
as the sheer size of the huge american market are enough to steer 
money into the united states 
yield or the return on a bond is among the first 
considerations for globally minded investors in deciding where to 
put their funds inflation rates rank high because no one wants to 
watch the worth of a fixedincome investment eroded by rising 
prices currency values also are crucial 
its more of a stew of events rather than one main course that 
we can sink our teeth into said robert brusca an economist at 
nikko securities co international inc 
