an ambitious multimedia effort aimed at 
hispanics gets underway monday enabling advertisers to reach the 
nations fastgrowing spanishspeaking market by magazine 
television and telephone 
creators of the service say 90 percent of the 10 million in 
annual ad time and space has been sold media analysts and 
competitors said the service could draw renewed attention to the 
spanishlanguage market 
some media and advertising executives have argued that us 
advertisers are missing a profitable opportunity by failing to 
spend more on reaching the 20 millionplus hispanics in the united 
states in their native language 
we frankly welcome this competition because we want to make 
spanish print media better known and accepted said alberto abdo 
a marketing executive with miamibased america publishing group a 
leading spanishlanguage publisher with 16 magazines sold in the 
united states 
the new multimedia service will reach an estimated 500000 
hispanic magazine readers and nearly 90 percent of hispanic homes 
with television says its developer whittle communications of 
knoxville tenn 
starting later this spring advertisers will also be mentioned 
when operators answer calls to a tollfree telephone service for 
hispanics seeking information on topics ranging from recipes to 
immigration the operator will answer calls by saying the hotline 
service is brought to you by 
among the sponsors who are paying 500000 a year under twoyear 
contracts for a basic package that includes television and 
telephone time and space in the magazine are american airlines 
procter amp gamble american telephone amp telegraph and kinney shoes 
the conerstone of the service is the magazine la familia de hoy 
published every other month it is distributed free to 10500 
medical waiting rooms and beauty parlors in hispanic neigborhoods 
in 45 markets 
whittle executives said the magazine will offer information that 
can help hispanics live better in the united states 
that is a big break from other spanishlanguage magazines 
circulated here that often rely mainly on gossip entertainment 
and fashion said editor patricia duarte 
the marchapril issue has stories on recognizing when your 
children may be abusing drugs and what to do about it handling 
finances cooking tips relating to your spouse and staying 
healthy it also has a profile of president bushs daughterinlaw 
colomba bush who is from mexico 
whittle is also producing twominute informational programs that 
will run 31 times a week on the spanishlanguage television network 
univision which reaches 64 million spanishspeaking households in 
the united states 
each program will identify the sponsor at the start and finish 
and include a commercial of 30 to 45 seconds many of the programs 
will be drawn from subjects covered in the magazine 
a typical program starts with an introduction by former 
univision network news anchor teresa rodriguez after the 
commercial an expert may discuss a topic often leaving a number 
or address for more information 
in one program a physician offers health tips for pregnant 
women in another ms rodriguez toured a museum designed for 
children 
f ashley shomaker who is overseesing the project for whittle 
said advertisers are also being mentioned at other times of the day 
on the univision network to draw attention to upcoming shows 
advertisers will also be rotated regularly on the telephone 
announcement 
richard hamilton an advertising executive with darcy masius 
benton amp bowles in new york said marketers are starting to pay 
more attention to the hispanic market because it is growing rapidly 
in size per capita income and willingness to buy recognized brands 
he said they are turning to spanishlanguage media because 
research indicates many hispanics prefer communications in 
spanish to english 
but america publishings abdo said that while hispanics make up 
nearly 10 percent of the us population advertisers spend less 
than 1 percent of their ad budgets in spanishlanguage media 
they spend mostly on tv the amounts dedicated to print are 
very low he said 
nonetheless he said ad pages at his companys magazines are up 
36 percent this year from a year ago he credited more aggressive 
marketing and greater awareness among advertisers of the markets 
potential 
