phone equipment from 1972 to 1980 by using illegal and 
anticompetitive activities 
at the time general dynamics owned general dynamics telephone 
systems center formerly strombergcarlson corp and general 
dynamics communications co the company sold its telecommunications 
business in 1982 
the settlement acknowledges that atampt and its subsidiaries did 
not act in collusion to prevent competition schildz said 
