<TEXT>
marathon petroleum co will make southeastern 
michigan a test market for a gasoline intended to help meet demands 
for reduced air pollution from autos the company said friday 
marathon will start selling its amaraclean gasolines monday 
in three unleaded grades at 161 stations in eight southeastern 
michigan counties 
if the gasolines sell in the detroit area marathon will start 
marketing them sometime next year in other cities such as 
cleveland st louis cincinnati and akron ohio the company said 
the introduction of cleaner gasolines has followed a proposal by 
president bush last june 5 that would have required selling 
millions of cars that run on fuels other than gasoline such as 
natural gas or methanol 
william reilly head of the environmental protection agency 
confirmed last month the bush administration was telling senate 
leaders that reformulated gasolines might be an acceptable 
alternative 
the compromise cleanair bill being debated in the senate this 
week would require reformulated cleanerburning gasolines in the 
countrys smoggiest cities by 1995 said charles gray head of the 
epas ann arbor testing laboratory 
atlantic richfield co already is selling reformulated gasoline 
in california in denver conoco and shamrock sell gasoline blended 
to reduce carbon monoxide emissions 
amoco isnt marketing a reformulated gasoline yet but that is 
a major consideration among the alternate fuels that are being 
looked at said spokesman neil geary in chicago 
geary said oil companies are experimenting with various fuels 
he said amoco expects within a month to begin test marketing 
compressed natural gas at four denver locations 
white said motorists probably wont notice any difference in 
price or performance with the amaraclean gasolines 
but the gasoline will evaporate less easily in hot weather 
cutting down on a major cause of smog 
the fuels are a step toward reduced volatility levels the epa 
proposes to require for all gasolines by 1992 gray said 
the fuel is also formulated to burn more completely and 
cancercausing chemicals normally used to boost octane have been 
eliminated marathon said the blends cut hydrocarbon emissions 
about 20 percent and carbon monoxide 14 percent 
</TEXT>
